The paper proposes a framework for network discovery using deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the task of vertex classification, which is a common problem in supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) since the paper deals with network discovery. The paper also uses concepts from artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures (cs.DS), and neural networks (cs.NE), which are all relevant to the proposed framework.
